Weekly Magazine for Citizens, no. 1, First Volume, October 1, 1793. A currently atypical innovative use of typographic design in the title field of the magazine. Werfel has wanted to signal that the magazine was for the entire broad middle class of self-employed and artisans, as well as "Citizens of the Jewish Nation". After January 1794, the magazine appeared with a more traditional title field, and under the apt title "Weekly Magazine for Citizens", because by omitting "the round figure" one could achieve "to gain more reading on each magazine".
